I am a survivor of domestic violence myself. I simply cannot in good faith support this production or any production, company, brand, organization, etc that works with, affiliates with, supports or defends Amber Heard! Amber Heard is a self admitted (refer to YouTube channel Incredibly Average to hear the multiple leaked audios for yourself!) abuser and has a history of prior abuse! How in the world does a movie studio, production company, brand, company, organization, etc decide to work with and therefore support, co-sign and align itself with an abuser in the year 2020, is beyond me! As a domestic violence survivor myself, it is my job to let these companies, brands, movies studios, organizations, etc know that this will NOT be tolerated or accepted at all, that there are consequences to your actions if you do this and that by doing this, it automatically makes you an abuse apologist AND enabler!! Is that the position you want to take & be known for?!? I think not!! 

As a domestic violence survivor, I stand with other survivors & current victims! I stand with male domestic violence survivors & current victims! Male DV survivors & current victims have to deal with the negative stigma that does with DV against males & the fear of not being believed simply bc they’re male, even more so when their abuser is female, they’re having to deal with incredibly sexist beliefs! I already know from my own experience how hard it is for us women DV survivors to be believed, I know that it’s even harder for males, simply due to them being male & even more so when their abuser is female! This is not something I will tolerate or accept & will passionately fight against, bc I stand with ALL DV survivors, not just females!! 

I stand w Johnny Depp, a DV survivor who is bravely stepping forward to tell his story & fight the good fight for ALL DV survivors & current victims, shedding an important light that DV can happen to anyone - even when you’re as rich, famous & beloved as Johnny is,  that males are victims of DV too and females can be abusers!! The way he’s been treated, vilified, hated, made fun of, had baseless accusations thrown at him & believed simply bc he’s male & they were coming from a female, is absolutely horrendous! 
It is a very dangerous msg to send to DV survivors & current victims & to male DV survivors/victims that you will not only not be believed, you will lose jobs, your career will be negatively affected, your reputation & good name will be negatively affected no matter how long & hard you worked to build it, if you come forward w your story of abuse! While at the same time, your abuser will be supported, will keep jobs and even get more jobs, companies-brands-organizations-jobs-the public will support your abuser & will participate in furthering the abuse from your abuser by participating in vilifying you, believing your abusers lies, attacking you & trying to ruin your career, good name & reputation! 
I stand w Johnny Depp, I believe Johnny Depp, Johnny Depp is innocent and a victim! Amber Heard is an abuser & anyone, any company, brand, organization, movie studio, job, etc who supports her, works w her, affiliates w her, is an abuse apologist & enabler! Amber Heard MUST be fired & held accountable & punished for what she’s done! Johnny Depp is the victim, he MUST be supported! Johnny deserves to have his roles in Fantastic Beasts & Pirates of the Caribbean (a franchise which was built off the back of Johnny’s sheer talent, brilliance, reputation & hard work!), if he so wishes! Until these things are done, I will NOT Ben supporting any brand, company, organization, movie studio, movies/TV shows, etc that reward Amber Heard and work w her, while revictimizing & punishing Johnny Depp, an actual victim!

Amber Heard has been exposed as a domestic abuser by Johnny Depp. In his $50 million lawsuit, Johnny Depp describes many incidents of domestic abuse that he suffered at the hands of his (then) wife Amber Heard, including one incident where she punched him twice in the face and another where she shattered his finger with a vodka bottle, and his finger had to be surgically reattached. He will bear the scar from that for the rest of his life. 

Also, Amber Heard was arrested in 2009 for abusing a former domestic partner, Tasya Van Ree, demonstrating a repeated pattern of abuse by Amber Heard.

Since Heard's divorce from Johnny Depp, she has systematically crusaded to ruin Depp in Hollywood, repeating multiple accounts of fake incidents in which she had actually abused Johnny Depp, but lied and created false accounts of him being the abuser. About the incident during which she shattered the bones in Johnny Depp's finger and nearly severed it, causing Depp to require surgery to reattach and repair it, Heard presented a false story claiming that he cut off his finger himself, dipped it in paint and scrawled obscenities all over the walls. 

Likewise, Heard recounts fabricated incidents of Johnny Depp hitting her in the face when she had, in fact, punched him. Though staff and neighbors in the building where she lived reported seeing no marks on her face in the hours and days after she says Johnny Depp hit her, yet she appeared in court six (6) days later with bruises on her face, asking for a temporary restraining order, which was granted. Photos of Heard from the very next day show her full face, without makeup, and not a single bruise.

As Amber Heard is a known and proven domestic abuser, Warner Brothers and DC Entertainment should and must remove Heard from their Aquaman 2 film project. They must not ignore the suffering of Heard's victims, and must not glamorize a domestic abuser. 

Men are victims of domestic abuse, just like women. This must be recognized, and action must be taken to prevent a known abuser from being celebrated within the entertainment industry.

Do the right thing. Remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2.
